  "body": "### Description\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\nThe number of unread messages in the app doesn't match the info in OSX dock bar.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1434\" alt=\"captura de pantalla 2018-11-09 a la s 10 53 02 a m\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37297779/48266377-f3281c00-e40d-11e8-8428-702e52b19667.png\">\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nTo show the same amount of unread messages both in the app and in the OSX dock bar.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n- Open Status Desktop\r\n- Wait until receiving a new message\r\n- Check dock bar\r\n\r\nFollowing https://github.com/status-im/status-react/pull/6888:\r\nThe home tab should indicate that there is activity going on (see proposed design). I think we will be repeating information by adding again the total amount of unread messages (already on dock). A simple \"dot\" could be used to indicate that there is activity going on. We could also use this for Profile when we need to get the user's attention. [Design proposal](https://www.figma.com/file/MRYBI5axcTwL4Ft8xAYhFOfy/Desktop-Chat?node-id=377%3A0):\r\n![group 19](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37297779/49243569-6eb53180-f3ec-11e8-8789-ee57e9da651f.png)\r\n\r\n![group 22](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37297779/49243622-87254c00-f3ec-11e8-8b51-95834b9982e4.png)\r\n\r\nSummary:\r\n[ ] - OSx dockebar should have amount of all unread messages\r\n[ ] - Home tab should have dot to indicate about any activity",
