    "body": "@EugeOrtiz \r\nI agree, we should either:\r\n**1)** show the dot if there's any activity for all the cases (no matter if that is 1-1 chat, group chat or a public chat)\r\n**2)** show the exact number of new messages, for all the cases (no matter if that is 1-1 chat, group chat or a public chat)\r\n\r\nRight now, we are showing only messages received in 1-1 chats and group chats, and it is confusing from user perspective.\r\nThe fact that logic for public chats is different from group chats - doesn't make sense, and is a bug even if we want to stay with the old logic. \r\n\r\n<img width=\"690\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/43638377/49284894-99f85900-f49e-11e8-9d2b-cabbdcfe6849.png\">\r\n\r\n@chadyj @churik @siphiuel @lukaszfryc what do you guys think?",
